    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Air Compressor and Power Steering
        Pump - Removal - Air Compressor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Air Compressor</title>
        <figure id="f3350009244" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK16/K16003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Air compressor mounting and connections</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M18 elbow assembly (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose (coolant) .50 ID (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air compressor (oil supply) hose assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 50 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drain hose (oil)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air compressor gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 80 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 elbow assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a drain pan under the air compressor assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clamp off coolant hoses so engine coolant does not drain out.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen coolant hose clamps and remove two coolant hoses from air compressor.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air compressor (oil supply) hose assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen oil drain hose clamps and remove drain hose.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cap oil and coolant lines to keep dirt out and reduce fluid spills.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M12 x 80 bolts holding air compressor to the front cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, get assistance to remove and install the air compressor and
                    power steering pump assembly.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Support weight of air compressor and remove two M12 x 50 bolts holding the air compressor
                and support bracket to the crankcase. Remove air compressor and bracket assembly from engine.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M10 x 30 bolts connecting the air compressor bracket to the air compressor.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard air compressor gasket, mounted between the air compressor and front
                cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
